.TH modbusMaskWrite 3lightmodbus "28 July 2016" "v1.2"
.SH NAME
.PP
\fBmodbusMaskWrite\fP \- write single bit to an array.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\fB\fC#include <lightmodbus/core.h>\fR
.PP
\fB\fCuint8_t modbusMaskWrite( uint8_t *mask, uint16_t maskLength, uint16_t bit, uint8_t value );\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fBmodbusMaskWrite\fP writes \fBbit\fP bit in \fBmask\fP little\-endian array of \fBmaskLength\fP length to \fBvalue\fP value. It's useful when whole array is
 one long bit mask. When returned value is greater than 0, an error occurred.
.SH SEE ALSO
